Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.48,0:00:13.86,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Has something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.70,0:00:20.79,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,There's absolutely no hope in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.79,0:00:22.68,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Is this about His Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.80,0:00:27.09,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Apparently, it's more in his nature to invade
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.09,0:00:30.94,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,and take control of another country\N instead of joining forces with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.88,0:00:33.98,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.18,0:00:37.09,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,He said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.51,0:01:01.95,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,At last, I've found him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.71,0:01:04.96,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,Someone who understands poison...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.28,0:01:09.26,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,a sovereign who might use it the right way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.98,0:02:55.45,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,If the negotiations with \NPrince Arnold fail like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.45,0:02:57.99,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Coyolles might be invaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.00,0:03:00.46,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,And if that happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.06,0:03:04.15,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,You're enthusiastic for \Nthis early in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.88,0:03:06.22,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Lord Lawvine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.53,0:03:10.08,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,But I see hesitation in your sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.02,0:03:14.14,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.80,0:03:17.46,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,my thoughts had turned \Nin an unworthy direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.90,0:03:20.22,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,By unworthy, you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.28,0:03:25.72,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,If one day we go to war with another country,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.28,0:03:29.25,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,everyone here will go \Ninto battle, won't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.92,0:03:31.06,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,They will.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.07,0:03:36.29,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I find myself afraid of a future like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.43,0:03:39.62,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,It's only natural to find it terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.62,0:03:40.49,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.15,0:03:45.21,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,My son lost his life in the last war.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.96,0:03:49.31,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,I'm proud of my son for fighting so bravely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.28,0:03:52.14,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.09,0:03:55.28,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,in equal measure to that sense of pride...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.97,0:03:58.81,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,I wish that my son had lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.75,0:04:01.18,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Lord Lawvine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.24,0:04:05.36,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,A war means that people will \Nbe robbed of their futures.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.36,0:04:06.76,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Others will steal them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.62,0:04:11.14,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,To conquer the fear of that, \None can only stand and fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.38,0:04:14.28,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Stand and fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.67,0:04:19.23,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,I mean that you shouldn't deny \Nyour own hopes and feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.86,0:04:24.15,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,You should use them as fuel to move forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.90,0:04:27.31,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,"What is it that I can do?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.98,0:04:29.93,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Find the answer to that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.36,0:04:35.73,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you, Lord Lawvine!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:04:38.28,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Then, I shall see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.10,0:04:45.84,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I don't want to die in some war.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.25,0:04:48.39,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I don't want Coyolles to fall into ruin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.22,0:04:51.68,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But that isn't all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.14,0:04:54.52,flashback,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rather than joining hands \Nwith another country,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.52,0:04:57.23,flashback,Arnold,0,0,0,,invading and taking control of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.55,0:04:59.44,flashback,Arnold,0,0,0,,that suits me much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.72,0:05:03.15,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,You aren't that kind of person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.78,0:05:06.76,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I want you to understand that, Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.96,0:05:15.75,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,And so, we have a special \Nobserver for your training,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.58,0:05:19.00,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,the Crown Prince of the Empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.68,0:05:21.90,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold Hein.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.90,0:05:24.51,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Why is Prince Arnold here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.80,0:05:35.89,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,No matter how you look at \Nthis, I've been found out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.39,0:05:40.68,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I want to see the trainees move.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.68,0:05:41.27,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.95,0:05:45.57,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Could this mean that he'll \Noverlook my actions?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.23,0:05:50.32,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.56,0:05:54.75,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,So, what exactly are you trying to do here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.75,0:05:57.10,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.81,0:06:03.01,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I am most pleased to meet you, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.01,0:06:06.22,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,That you would personally speak \Nto a mere knight candidate
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.22,0:06:09.05,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,makes me feel both humbled and delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.52,0:06:10.80,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.80,0:06:14.01,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,If you are not the person I think you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.36,0:06:19.31,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,then that would mean there is \Nno issue with my touching you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.88,0:06:29.73,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Come now. Quickly, try to refute it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.97,0:06:33.64,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold, please step away for a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.64,0:06:34.41,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.41,0:06:36.88,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,If you continue, someone is sure to see!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.88,0:06:38.24,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Is there some problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.24,0:06:39.28,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes, there is!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.28,0:06:40.67,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.99,0:06:45.42,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Y-You have a fiancée, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.19,0:06:49.66,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Well, yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.66,0:06:51.55,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,You do, don't you? I thought so!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.55,0:06:53.05,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.05,0:06:57.73,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,your manner of speech is quite disrespectful \Nfor a mere knight candidate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.93,0:07:01.00,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,My deepest apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.00,0:07:03.86,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I don't know what it is \Nyou're apologizing for.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.26,0:07:07.55,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Tell me with your own lips what you've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.38,0:07:12.94,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I-I didn't tell Your Highness \Nanything and dressed as a boy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.94,0:07:15.76,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,so I could join the knight \Ncandidates' training!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.76,0:07:17.83,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I am truly, very sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.48,0:07:19.70,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.03,0:07:24.75,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,But why are you doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.99,0:07:27.08,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.42,0:07:30.98,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,this training you've thought up...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.98,0:07:33.95,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I wanted to undergo it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.62,0:07:41.54,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,If you wish to continue, \Nthere are conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.00,0:07:45.03,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You must be sure to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.03,0:07:48.30,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,And make sure that no one \Nfinds out your gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.30,0:07:48.87,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.44,0:07:50.56,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Can you keep to those?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.56,0:07:52.65,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.72,0:07:58.94,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Are you enjoying this training that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.94,0:07:59.66,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.04,0:08:04.04,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold, the training you've \Nthought up is truly magnificent!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.40,0:08:07.92,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your intention to carefully help the \Nknights to grow comes through clearly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.86,0:08:11.28,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Capable people are the empire's treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.04,0:08:19.82,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But sending these knights into \Nbattle in the future will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.11,0:08:26.00,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I overheard your conversation \Nwith Prince Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.00,0:08:27.22,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I'm sure you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.00,0:08:31.58,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I believe I can predict what you're thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.33,0:08:34.63,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You believe that we should \Nform an alliance with Coyolles
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.63,0:08:36.82,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,and you're going to try to \Nconvince me, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.70,0:08:41.40,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,But there is no value in a country \Nthat has lost all its power.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.08,0:08:44.88,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,When a nation's collapse \Nis only a matter of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.88,0:08:47.71,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,the only question is how \Nto deal the final blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.76,0:08:54.09,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold, from time to time \Nyou are the most incredible liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.68,0:08:58.85,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You're free to think \Nwhatever you like of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.17,0:09:00.25,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,but remember this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:05.33,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,For this empire, war is not a cruel choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.54,0:09:08.67,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's simply one means of politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.16,0:09:24.51,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,The first time I met Prince \NKyle was when I was a trader.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.00,0:09:29.29,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,In this rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.59,0:09:32.84,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,protecting your wares on the road \Nmust have been very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.71,0:09:35.89,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,Our kingdom lacks material resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.89,0:09:40.43,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,It's traders like you who support us and \Nallow us to preserve our daily lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.20,0:09:45.68,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,I wish to express my deepest \Nrespect and gratitude to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.12,0:09:47.76,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Though he was a member of the royal family,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.76,0:09:52.00,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,he was someone who treated people \Nof different stations with respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.99,0:09:57.34,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,The second time I met him was \Nin my life as an herbalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.00,0:10:00.92,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Then, too, he was someone who acted \Nfrom his heart when dealing with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.59,0:10:03.45,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,And the third time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.86,0:10:07.25,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,I will speak with my father \Nabout the research funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.77,0:10:11.00,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,Because I know that \Nyou two will produce results.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.77,0:10:14.33,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,I swear that I will make him agree!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.46,0:10:17.63,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,It worked?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:20.17,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.17,0:10:23.97,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,More than anything else, the fact that your \Nunwavering hard work has been rewarded
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.97,0:10:25.67,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,makes me truly happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.31,0:10:32.90,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,It's because Prince Kyle is like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.42,0:10:34.46,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,that I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.64,0:10:45.25,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness, starting today, I'd like \Nyou to start taking these pills as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.25,0:10:48.04,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Though, the flavor is just as awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.37,0:10:51.51,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,If it means that this body \Nof mine will move properly,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.51,0:10:53.42,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,then it's nothing to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.91,0:11:00.32,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Kyle, the truth is that \Nat the party the other evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.32,0:11:04.95,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I happened to overhear your \Nconversation with Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.83,0:11:09.45,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,You saw me in a most embarrassing situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.45,0:11:12.97,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,In truth, the polite thing to do would \Nhave been to leave the country after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.97,0:11:16.32,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,However, I cannot afford to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.32,0:11:19.51,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Didn't you think that it might be dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.51,0:11:24.49,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,During the war, Prince Arnold beheaded \Nmembers of royal families of enemy nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.49,0:11:25.87,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,You're aware of that, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.30,0:11:31.88,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Everything from the fruits of Prince \NArnold's battles to his political measures...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.88,0:11:33.66,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I've investigated everything I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.24,0:11:36.90,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,It seems to have been \Ncamouflaged very cleverly,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.45,0:11:39.81,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,but the care shown for the common \Npeople in domestic policies...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.81,0:11:42.84,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I'm certain that it's his \Nintention at work there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.44,0:11:46.88,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Killing the monarchs of enemy \Nlands in the last war...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.88,0:11:50.73,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,it was done to prevent the seeds of further \Ntrouble. It was a form of compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.03,0:11:52.58,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,That's how I think of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.92,0:11:55.96,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,And, the reality is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.56,0:11:58.77,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,even if His Highness is a \Ncruel and barbarous person,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.32,0:12:01.65,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,it doesn't change what I must do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.55,0:12:08.00,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I have a request to make of you, Prince Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.51,0:12:14.25,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Won't you first form a \Nmodest alliance with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.25,0:12:15.74,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,An alliance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.77,0:12:19.37,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,In order to convince Prince Arnold,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.21,0:12:22.47,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I will need your strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.64,0:12:36.02,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.79,0:12:39.78,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Everything in it was incredibly intriguing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.18,0:12:42.62,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You love to learn, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.62,0:12:43.94,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes, very much so!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.46,0:12:48.28,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Learning new things, whatever they \Nmight be, makes me very excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.28,0:12:50.70,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The world gets wider and wider,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.70,0:12:53.58,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,and even the view I saw yesterday \Nlooks different to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.26,0:12:56.96,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,That settles it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.55,0:13:01.07,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You aren't suited to be an empress.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.48,0:13:03.99,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.99,0:13:06.30,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You should just come and join me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.87,0:13:11.47,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,If you did, then if there were anything \Nyou didn't know, I would teach you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.47,0:13:13.65,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you for your invitation,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.65,0:13:17.69,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,but I am here to marry Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.38,0:13:20.69,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Arnold Hein, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.36,0:13:23.66,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I understand why you're drawn to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.88,0:13:27.95,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I'm interested in him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.67,0:13:32.68,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,It seems he's turned down Kyle's request.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.34,0:13:36.96,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,And the reasons he gave for his refusal \Nwere exactly the sort of thing I love.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.44,0:13:42.06,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,If it were Arnold Hein, then I have the \Nfeeling that he'd use it quite effectively...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.68,0:13:47.47,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,this compound I've created, \Nwhich I call black powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.45,0:13:51.28,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I've been looking for so long!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.76,0:13:55.60,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I never imagined that I'd meet \Nthe right person in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.68,0:14:02.47,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Despite his appearance, His \NHighness is a very kind person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.47,0:14:05.82,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even if he said some harsh \Nwords to Prince Kyle,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.82,0:14:08.36,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,it's likely that he didn't truly—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.11,0:14:08.36,top,Michel,0,0,0,,Say, Rishe!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.36,0:14:10.24,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Will you help me meet with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.15,0:14:12.49,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.85,0:14:16.83,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'll see if he can make \Nsome time for you soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.83,0:14:18.62,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Then, let's go and see him right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.87,0:14:22.20,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,His Highness is very \Nbusy, so a sudden visi—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.47,0:14:25.53,top,Michel,0,0,0,,If he's as kind as you say, \Nthen I'm sure he'd forgive us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.59,0:14:27.94,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Well, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.94,0:14:29.13,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.60,0:14:32.39,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,The truth is that you don't want \Nme to meet with him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.90,0:14:39.07,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.73,0:14:43.90,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,haven't asked me what \Nblack powder is, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.31,0:14:53.24,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,The professor told me all \Nabout black powder...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.71,0:14:56.04,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,back in my third life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.36,0:14:59.88,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,So, you won't cease your \Nexperiments, no matter what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.85,0:15:02.29,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.53,0:15:06.21,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,Not even if it means that many \Npeople will lose their lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.16,0:15:11.61,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,"That which humans have created \Nmust be used the right way."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.89,0:15:15.10,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,There's a problem with this warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.43,0:15:22.21,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Which is that no one can accurately \Ndefine what "the right way" is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.32,0:15:29.41,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,If this black powder of \Nmine is used the right way,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.41,0:15:31.71,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,I'm sure that this world \Nwould easily be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.40,0:15:35.58,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,But would that really be wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.71,0:15:42.71,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,"How will the things I \Ncreate change the world?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.99,0:15:47.06,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Is wanting to see that \Nreally such a bad thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.56,0:15:50.94,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.95,0:15:59.32,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Farewell, my student.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.46,0:16:05.30,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,I sincerely hope that your life
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.76,0:16:08.48,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,will unfold in a way that you feel is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.16,0:16:16.30,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I couldn't accept this black powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.10,0:16:21.37,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,It will turn the world on \Nits head and scramble it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.37,0:16:26.38,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I've been looking for a leader capable \Nof using it for so very, very long!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.00,0:16:29.43,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,A leader like Arnold Hein.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.21,0:16:44.35,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I must find a way to establish friendly \Nrelations between Coyolles and Galkhein.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.35,0:16:47.88,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,And with Professor Michel in that state,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.88,0:16:51.53,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,he'll stop at nothing to \Napproach Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.53,0:16:54.28,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,If he does, then His Highness will \Nuse black powder in the war and—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.69,0:17:00.38,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Theodore?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.71,0:17:04.46,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I heard he found out. About \Nyou dressing as a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.01,0:17:08.74,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.18,0:17:12.46,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I had mixed feelings about you being \Nable to completely deceive my brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.46,0:17:14.06,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,so I don't particularly mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.63,0:17:18.16,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Still, the news reached you very quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.16,0:17:20.92,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Well, my retainers are \Noutstanding, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.92,0:17:24.52,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Whatever my brother does, no matter \Nwhere he is, I know about it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.52,0:17:27.15,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I have a perfect information network set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.63,0:17:29.58,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,And it isn't just my big \Nbrother I hear about.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.13,0:17:32.16,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I've got my sister-in-law in there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.16,0:17:35.39,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I've already looked into the \Nbackgrounds of the knight candidates.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.39,0:17:38.97,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,If anything happened to you, I \Nwouldn't know how to face my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.66,0:17:41.60,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.60,0:17:45.08,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,It's nothing. And it's not \Nthat I'm worried for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.08,0:17:47.38,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I'm doing this for my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.85,0:17:50.14,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.67,0:17:58.06,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Actually, I have a favor to \Nask of you, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.30,0:18:03.93,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,May I borrow your outstanding \Nretainers for a short while?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.36,0:18:08.61,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Is it something that will help my brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.61,0:18:12.57,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,No. In fact, it would be an act of \Nrebellion against Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.52,0:18:15.97,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.97,0:18:18.37,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Since it sounds like fun, I'll join you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.07,0:18:21.58,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then, we've come to an understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.06,0:18:40.52,flashback,Michel's father,0,0,0,,Because you were born,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.52,0:18:42.71,flashback,Michel's father,0,0,0,,my wife is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.38,0:18:47.10,flashback,Michel's father,0,0,0,,Which is why you must atone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.43,0:18:52.75,flashback,Michel's father,0,0,0,,You were born to bring us misfortune, \Nyou harbinger of death!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.88,0:18:57.61,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,Whether I was hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.86,0:18:59.23,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,or I was lonely...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.76,0:19:02.51,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,the field of learning always accepted me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.16,0:19:08.22,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,Knowledge swiftly entered my \Nmind and settled into my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.12,0:19:13.33,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,It was just like breathing, \Nor drinking water.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.60,0:19:17.88,flashback,Michel's father,0,0,0,,This child has inherited my genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.65,0:19:21.41,flashback,Michel's father,0,0,0,,Use him as much as you like in my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.41,0:19:25.22,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,After being allowed into the \Nlaboratory, my world expanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.43,0:19:30.16,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,If I wanted to know something and \Nperformed enough experiments...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.16,0:19:32.55,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,my efforts would always be repaid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:36.27,flashback,researcher 1,0,0,0,,What is going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.27,0:19:41.07,flashback,researcher 2,0,0,0,,To think he'd be so adept at making\N something that would kill people...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.70,0:19:44.18,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,After some time, a war broke out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.20,0:19:47.04,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,Everything burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.43,0:19:50.63,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,All of the alchemists in the laboratory...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.07,0:19:54.70,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,everyone, including my \Nfather, lost their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.36,0:20:01.80,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,It was by chance that I created it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.93,0:20:06.41,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,A compound capable of destroying everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.88,0:20:14.94,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,That was black powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.40,0:20:19.28,flashback,Michel's father,0,0,0,,You truly are a harbinger of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.63,0:20:22.63,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,It's just as my father said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.63,0:20:26.60,italics,Michel; internal,0,0,0,,It seems I've been born to \Nbring misfortune to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.67,0:20:46.39,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,In the past, I was unable to \Nconvince Professor Michel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.30,0:20:52.64,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.23,0:20:56.68,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Well, hello, Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.60,0:21:00.38,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Have you managed to find a \Nway for me to meet with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.52,0:21:08.12,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor, do you truly intend to \Ngive black powder to Prince Arnold?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.39,0:21:14.66,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,If something has been born as a poison,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.66,0:21:17.63,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,then only in fulfilling its task\N will it find its true place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.57,0:21:24.31,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Everything, no matter what, must fulfill \Nthe role for which it was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.71,0:21:29.19,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,My own existence is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.85,0:21:33.10,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,A person who was born to \Nupset the ways of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.37,0:21:36.43,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,must act in accordance with that duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.80,0:21:41.93,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Even back in my third life, the \Nprofessor said these same things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.36,0:21:48.30,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even if many people will \Nlose their lives for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.30,0:21:49.42,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.24,0:21:52.54,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Black powder's reason for being...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.54,0:21:54.71,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,is to bring misfortune to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.44,0:22:01.12,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.12,0:22:03.70,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,It isn't that I want to \Nsay mean things to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.38,0:22:06.42,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,That's the honest truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.68,0:22:13.12,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,This is the calling I've been given.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.97,0:22:20.81,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I'm certain that the professor will \Nuse any means necessary to give
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.81,0:22:22.35,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,black powder to Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.49,0:22:26.44,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Good night, Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.07,0:22:30.50,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,If things keep going this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.07,0:22:34.00,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I won't be able to stop the professor.
